metadata.description: Painting of millet rat, by Qi Baishi (January 1, 1864 to September 16, 1957). He worked as a carpenter in his early years and then made a living selling paintings. At the age of 57, he settled in Beijing. He is good at painting flowers and birds, insects and fish, landscapes and figures, with vigorous and moist ink, rich and bright colors, simple and vivid modeling, and plain artistic conception. The year of the rat is coming, and Qi Baishi is commemorated here.
metadata.name: Painting of millet rat
